        finally, it's looking like some movement is taking place in the top 40! i love manchild, ik she's seen as overplayed btu i'd say she's up there with the best of the artists ruling the charts the past few years, so i'll happily welcome another number one from her (especially over alex warren). 'just keep watching' is a confusing one because i think tate mcrae has had so many better offerings recently but it's not terrible and i like what she brings to pop music today. 'dior' is your standard summer dance hit, don't hate it but don't love it either, same with 'can't decide'. 'sapphire' is absolutely awful. 'nice to each other' isn't spectacular but it's chill and catchy, olivia dean is obviously very talented too so i'm happy her platform is widening. 'fame is a gun' is one of my favourite songs of the year, super fun and inspired. i'm just happy we're finally getting some new hits!
